<br>
I, too, have gotten different advice from different people about the AA points.  Most people have always said don't bother with it till you're 60.  But that advice was also before PoP expansion.  Now there's a new level cap, new higher level AA options and the bar has been raised significantly (WAY over us!).  Because of that, there are certain AA skills I'd really like to have on my way to the big SIX-Oh.  Like run-speed 3.  Probably not a concern for you, but as Necro who must bum sows all his life or do an AC camp (a lifetime unto itself) Run3 is VERY important.  <br>
<br>
As a class who frequently solos, here is my personal regret.  For a couple months I did nothing but kill in Highkeep.  The experience was INSANE!  But finally, I leveled to 57 and the gravy train was over.  Looking back, I seriously wish I had had Luclin back at 55, cause I would have spent a couple extra weeks and soaked in at least 3 AA points.  I would have had 6 by now, and be working on those cool Class Specific powers.  <br>
<br>
So, I say if you find a place with incredible experience, milk it for some AA points.  When you get to your upper 50's you'll be that much ahead of the game.  Also, I've been moving the % of exp to AA up and down, depending on what I've wanted to accomplish.  I think I'll always have at least 10% going to AA tho.<br>
<br>
 <p>Sytox 57 Defiler<br>
