<br>
Im not exactly sure if you have and even greater chance at skilling up while fighting a Yellow or Red con though.  <br>
<br>
The best way to go about getting low weapon skills up is to  use your Free Training points that you get every lvl (if you have been saving them).  This does start to get expensive however as the trainer charges you after skill lvl 15 on every Training point.  <br>
Or you could do what i do and wait until you get a Kick Arse group, where the mobs are going down so fast and furiously that i will not matter if you switch to the weapon that you need to skill up (in your case the 2hs).  Best to ask your group if this is OK with them first, but most people will not mind in the least.  This is exactly what Karpe and Jokey were doing last night while we were fighting Hill Giants.  Skilling up thier 2hb.<br>
<br>
I also know that their seems to be some skills (not weapon skills) that can be advanced against Green type Mobs Such as pickpocket for Rogues and i think Instill doubt for Monks?  Correct me if im wrong Karpe.  Not sure why this is but it happens.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
<br>
Your Pally,<br>
Montag <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aevetare>Aevetare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Officer</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#000080>(11/30/02 8:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Q&amp;A spot</span><hr size=1> I too focused my weapon skill primarily in 2HS, and now am stuck trying to get my other weapon skills up.  It DOES appear that the skills only go up when the mobs are dark blue or higher, which limits when I can work on the skills.  The best time I have been able to do it has been on large raids, where there are 50 people fighting the mobs and my feeble efforts wont be really missed (or noticed!).<br>
<br>
I have also worked on them when I was hunting for xp with Sytox.  Granted, I asked him first if it was alright, and even then I found myself switching back to my main weapon when things got rough.  It is not something you can just focus on entirely in that situation.<br>
<br>
As far as AA, I pretty much have only started the AA thing now that most of my toons have hit 54 -- the leveling is really slow at this point and it is nice to at least see some progess.  With Aevetare I have gone 100% AA now that he is slightly into lvl 53 -- only so that I can die and get back to lvl 52 so I can go on Vox raids to try to get that last book I need.  Otherwise, I would've been 54 with Aev a long time ago too.  I think the AA points are a personal choice --  I would expect that some people won't mess with them until they are lvl 60, but others will see more benefit out of them earlier.<br>
<br>
Aev. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aevetare>Aevetare</A> at: 11/30/02 8:14:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tjsonoftark>tj son of tark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arrow of Light</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000080>(12/1/02 10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Q&amp;A spot</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for the responses.  They were very helpful. As to the first question it seems that you all were correct.  I have been trying to raise my 2hs soloing, because I thought it would not be very helpful to a group using a weaker skill.  But right after I posted I went into Echo Caverns and joined a group. I asked if they would mind if I worked on my 2hs.  Well, it was a &quot;killer group&quot;, I raised my skill from 61 to 118 in just three hours.  So you are correct &quot;work with a group, ask permission, and go for it&quot;.<br>
